1
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:43,600
Mom

2
00:01:14,560 --> 00:01:16,159
Even though your panic disorder

3
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:17,719
seems stable for now,

4
00:01:17,840 --> 00:01:19,400
you still have to take your meds on time,

5
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:21,519
or if something unusual happens,

6
00:01:21,519 --> 00:01:22,760
you could have a stress reaction.

7
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:24,319
Panic disorder?

8
00:01:24,840 --> 00:01:26,439
Sheng Yuanzhou has been sick all along.

9
00:01:42,799 --> 00:01:43,359
Mom!

10
00:01:44,239 --> 00:01:44,920
Mom!

11
00:01:46,799 --> 00:01:47,519
What's wrong?

12
00:01:47,879 --> 00:01:49,519
Why is the washer making so many suds?

13
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:51,040
Oh my God.

14
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:52,359
How much detergent did you put in?

15
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:53,799
I only put in one bag.

16
00:01:54,359 --> 00:01:55,079
One bag?

17
00:01:56,319 --> 00:01:57,480
Here, let me handle it.

18
00:01:58,200 --> 00:01:59,480
Go start the rice in the kitchen.

19
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:02,200
Put it in the pot.

20
00:02:03,239 --> 00:02:04,040
In the pot.

21
00:02:04,040 --> 00:02:04,640
Go on.

22
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:05,480
Okay.

23
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:30,159
Look at you.

24
00:02:38,159 --> 00:02:38,879
Are you crazy?

25
00:02:40,479 --> 00:02:41,800
What are you doing? I'm cooking!

26
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:44,639
Cooking?

27
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:47,000
Looks like you're trying to burn it down.

28
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:48,400
Cooking? Watch closely.

29
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:55,080
This is how you use a rice cooker properly.

30
00:02:55,520 --> 00:02:56,639
So it's that simple.

31
00:02:57,039 --> 00:02:58,520
What a genius.

32
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,120
No idea how you survived all these years

33
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:00,919
living like this.

34
00:03:01,159 --> 00:03:01,960
None of your business.

35
00:03:06,520 --> 00:03:07,560
How did you get in?

36
00:03:08,319 --> 00:03:09,240
You left the front door open.

37
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:10,319
How else do you think I got in?

38
00:03:13,039 --> 00:03:14,000
Then what are you here for?

39
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,400
At Prosperity Group,

40
00:03:16,039 --> 00:03:17,159
I got you a job.

41
00:03:18,479 --> 00:03:18,840
I'm not going.

42
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:19,800
Why not?

43
00:03:21,919 --> 00:03:22,800
I've decided

44
00:03:23,759 --> 00:03:24,439
I'm not working anymore.

45
00:03:24,680 --> 00:03:26,199
I've tried way too many jobs.

46
00:03:26,599 --> 00:03:28,199
Catching chickens, hauling cargo,

47
00:03:28,599 --> 00:03:29,439
even delivering takeout.

48
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:31,000
I'm really sick of it.

49
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:31,639
So I

50
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:34,039
decided to be a writer.

51
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:34,840
Write novels.

52
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:36,960
Come on, take a look.

53
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:37,599
Look.

54
00:03:37,919 --> 00:03:39,159
Look at your family's situation.

55
00:03:39,319 --> 00:03:40,719
Who can afford to support you writing?

56
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:43,520
My parents didn't object.

57
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:44,879
You're the one making a fuss.

58
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:45,960
Look at your dad.

59
00:03:46,199 --> 00:03:46,879
He doesn't work,

60
00:03:47,199 --> 00:03:48,360
and he's been a loser his whole life.

61
00:03:48,759 --> 00:03:49,439
Sheng Yuanzhou.

62
00:03:49,599 --> 00:03:51,360
Who are you to come here and boss us around?

63
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:52,120
And criticize my dad?

64
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:53,840
Life isn't just about making money, okay?

65
00:03:54,439 --> 00:03:55,560
Being happy matters too.

66
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:56,639
So your happiness

67
00:03:57,599 --> 00:03:59,400
is built on your mom's suffering, right?

68
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:00,120
You...

69
00:04:01,159 --> 00:04:02,360
Why are you here again?

70
00:04:02,879 --> 00:04:03,599
Honestly...

71
00:04:05,159 --> 00:04:06,080
Sorry, Mom.

72
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,280
I messed it up again.

73
00:04:07,520 --> 00:04:08,199
It's okay.

74
00:04:08,199 --> 00:04:09,240
I already cleaned it up.

75
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:10,199
It's fine.

76
00:04:13,039 --> 00:04:14,680
Don't come here and hurt my child.

77
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:18,199
Think it over carefully.

78
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:22,639
Even if I get a job, I don't need your help.

79
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:23,199
Leave. Now.

80
00:04:23,839 --> 00:04:24,399
Go. Now.

81
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,000
Go, now! Go!

82
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:28,759
Go! Go!

83
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:34,800
I'll be back soon.

84
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:36,600
I'll come back with money.

85
00:04:40,319 --> 00:04:40,920
Mortgage it?

86
00:04:41,199 --> 00:04:41,639
Yeah.

87
00:04:42,600 --> 00:04:44,160
I want to mortgage that land my mom left me.

88
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:44,800
Put it up as collateral.

89
00:04:45,079 --> 00:04:46,079
Why not just sell it?

90
00:04:46,439 --> 00:04:47,959
I heard the bonded zone's relocating.

91
00:04:48,120 --> 00:04:49,600
Keeping that land will just lose you money.

92
00:04:50,120 --> 00:04:51,639
And a few days ago I met this

93
00:04:51,639 --> 00:04:52,920
newly rich coal miner from Xinjiang.

94
00:04:53,160 --> 00:04:54,199
He's dumb and loaded.

95
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:55,360
I'll sweet-talk him a bit,

96
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:56,560
you sell him that land,

97
00:04:56,879 --> 00:04:58,399
and I'll only take five percent.

98
00:04:58,680 --> 00:04:59,120
How about it?

99
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,959
That's Sheng Yuanzhou's mom's gravesite.

100
00:05:06,079 --> 00:05:06,800
Forget it.

101
00:05:07,519 --> 00:05:08,480
I'll mortgage it instead.

102
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:11,040
Help me negotiate a better price.

103
00:05:11,439 --> 00:05:12,360
When I make money trading stocks,

104
00:05:13,079 --> 00:05:14,120
you'll still get your five percent.

105
00:05:14,759 --> 00:05:15,920
That's nothing.

106
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:17,639
Just consider that I owe you a favor.

107
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:21,399
You owe me way too many favors already.

108
00:05:21,639 --> 00:05:22,519
How are you gonna pay them back?

109
00:05:23,079 --> 00:05:24,199
How do you want me to?

110
00:05:25,519 --> 00:05:26,879
A favor for a favor...

111
00:05:28,639 --> 00:05:29,519
Pay with your body.

112
00:05:32,639 --> 00:05:34,759
With Sheng Yuanzhou's identity backing me,

113
00:05:35,199 --> 00:05:37,759
even this body of mine looks tempting now.

114
00:05:43,839 --> 00:05:44,279
Look.

115
00:05:44,959 --> 00:05:46,199
Pretty handsome, right?

116
00:05:46,199 --> 00:05:47,920
Then why do you eat boxed lunches here?

117
00:05:48,759 --> 00:05:49,759
No money, obviously.

118
00:05:50,079 --> 00:05:51,040
His family's really poor.

119
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:54,000
I heard he works in the cafeteria to get by.

120
00:05:54,319 --> 00:05:55,800
Every day he secretly packs up leftovers.

121
00:05:55,959 --> 00:05:56,720
Leftovers?

122
00:05:57,160 --> 00:05:57,639
To feed the dog?

123
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:59,519
To feed a family of four.

124
00:06:00,759 --> 00:06:01,680
No wonder.

125
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:04,000
I smelled something stinky.

126
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:05,399
That kind of guy won't do.

127
00:06:05,839 --> 00:06:06,600
Exactly.

128
00:06:08,800 --> 00:06:10,040
I'll leave the mortgage to you.

129
00:06:10,680 --> 00:06:11,839
I've got something to do. I'm leaving.

130
00:06:24,279 --> 00:06:26,399
He's decided to mortgage Bai Zimei's land.

131
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:33,279
As long as I've got this as seed money,

132
00:06:34,439 --> 00:06:36,360
Before I turn back into Zhang Xiaobei,

133
00:06:36,879 --> 00:06:37,920
I'll definitely save up enough money.

134
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:39,600
Then

135
00:06:40,279 --> 00:06:41,160
Mom, Dad, and I

136
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:42,480
won't have to live a hard life anymore.

137
00:06:43,439 --> 00:06:45,800
No one will look down on me, Zhang Xiaobei, again.

138
00:07:13,839 --> 00:07:14,839
You?

139
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:16,000
I was about to ask you that.

140
00:07:16,399 --> 00:07:16,800
What are you doing?

141
00:07:17,639 --> 00:07:19,480
I was just heading home and you caught me.

142
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:24,920
Then don't act so sneaky.

143
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:29,120
It's because it reeks!

144
00:07:29,519 --> 00:07:31,759
I covered up because I didn't want anyone to see.

145
00:07:32,079 --> 00:07:32,879
Where have you been?

146
00:07:32,879 --> 00:07:33,639
Why do you smell so stinky?

147
00:07:33,639 --> 00:07:34,519
Did you fall into a cesspit?

148
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:36,199
It's all that crooked restaurant's fault.

149
00:07:45,920 --> 00:07:46,519
What are you doing?

150
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,480
Boss, this tofu's gone bad.

151
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:49,160
I'll toss it out.

152
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,199
This is hairy tofu.

153
00:07:51,199 --> 00:07:52,600
Hairy tofu is fine.

154
00:07:53,079 --> 00:07:54,959
Boss, you can't just for a little profit

155
00:07:54,959 --> 00:07:55,839
throw your conscience away.

156
00:07:56,680 --> 00:07:58,040
Customers will get stomachaches from it.

157
00:07:58,319 --> 00:07:59,920
Can't you understand plain language?

158
00:08:00,240 --> 00:08:01,959
It's safe to eat.

159
00:08:01,959 --> 00:08:04,360
Boss, selling expired food will get you arrested.

160
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:05,639
If you keep this up, I'll report you.

161
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:07,800
Are you out of your mind today?

162
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:08,560
Give it to me.

163
00:08:09,079 --> 00:08:09,519
Give it to me!

164
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:12,959
Get out, now. Get out!

165
00:08:17,759 --> 00:08:19,160
You're really something.

166
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:21,399
You threw away another perfectly good job.

167
00:08:21,959 --> 00:08:23,120
That boss was really nice.

168
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,399
Whenever there were leftover ingredients,

169
00:08:25,680 --> 00:08:26,480
he let me take them home.

170
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:27,839
How do you know?

171
00:08:28,199 --> 00:08:28,439
I...

172
00:08:31,879 --> 00:08:32,720
Why so many questions?

173
00:08:32,879 --> 00:08:33,879
Let's go, it stinks.

174
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,120
I get caught by you every time.

175
00:08:46,399 --> 00:08:47,840
The rainy-day video.

176
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:51,679
Is all this aimed at Sheng Yuanzhou,

177
00:08:52,679 --> 00:08:53,840
or aimed at me?

178
00:08:54,759 --> 00:08:55,840
If it's aimed at me,

179
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:58,000
then maybe besides me,

180
00:08:58,279 --> 00:08:59,000
there are other people

181
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,600
who know the Key of Fate exists.

182
00:09:02,159 --> 00:09:04,080
Sheng Yuanzhou showed up there...

183
00:09:04,799 --> 00:09:06,200
Was it really just a coincidence?

184
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:09,159
Or was he behind all this...

185
00:09:11,919 --> 00:09:12,360
Come in.

186
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:15,679
Young Master, your father wants you in the study.

187
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:17,039
Got it.

188
00:09:20,679 --> 00:09:24,000
I heard you got a hotel room with Zhu Yutong.

189
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:26,440
Yes.

190
00:09:26,879 --> 00:09:29,720
You never had a habit of playing women.

191
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:31,720
After Zhu Zipeng was arrested,

192
00:09:32,399 --> 00:09:33,279
control of the Zhu family

193
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:35,679
fell into Zhu Yutong's hands.

194
00:09:36,559 --> 00:09:37,919
She's good at socializing,

195
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:39,080
with a wide network.

196
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:40,679
I think getting closer to her

197
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:41,799
won't hurt.

198
00:09:42,159 --> 00:09:43,399
And the Lin family's dignity?

199
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:44,600
You still need to consider it.

200
00:09:45,039 --> 00:09:47,200
Lin Chengren has already come to me.

201
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:50,279
What do you think we should do?

202
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:53,480
How about we

203
00:09:54,039 --> 00:09:54,919
call off the engagement.

204
00:09:58,039 --> 00:09:59,000
A man

205
00:09:59,120 --> 00:10:00,639
just fooling around with a woman,

206
00:10:00,639 --> 00:10:02,639
and you let them make a fuss, then cancel it?

207
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:04,600
What about the Sheng family's reputation?

208
00:10:06,159 --> 00:10:07,279
Go to the Lin family right now.

209
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:08,480
Settle this for me.

210
00:10:09,399 --> 00:10:09,919
Actually,

211
00:10:10,720 --> 00:10:12,240
I don't feel anything for Lin Siqi.

212
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:15,120
You think marriage runs on feelings?

213
00:10:15,399 --> 00:10:15,960
I'm telling you,

214
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:18,039
whether you like Lin Siqi or not,

215
00:10:18,559 --> 00:10:19,639
the matter between the Sheng and Lin families

216
00:10:19,840 --> 00:10:20,720
is already decided.

217
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:23,919
Looks like calling it off won't be that easy.

218
00:10:32,559 --> 00:10:33,440
With you showing up like this,

219
00:10:34,039 --> 00:10:34,799
are you here to visit the sick?

220
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:36,639
You're joking.

221
00:10:37,279 --> 00:10:38,399
About last time at the hotel,

222
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:39,519
sorry about that.

223
00:10:40,559 --> 00:10:42,559
So I came to apologize to your dad.

224
00:10:42,879 --> 00:10:43,440
It's fine.

225
00:10:44,879 --> 00:10:46,639
Good for my dad to face the truth sooner.

226
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:48,320
Now we're even.

227
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:49,559
Fair enough.

228
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:51,519
If you can talk your dad into it,

229
00:10:52,039 --> 00:10:52,600
that's best.

230
00:10:54,159 --> 00:10:54,840
I'm confident I can.

231
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:57,320
Then these fruits...

232
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:58,759
take them in.

233
00:10:59,320 --> 00:11:00,159
At least it shows I came.

234
00:11:03,519 --> 00:11:04,039
Thanks.

235
00:11:08,039 --> 00:11:08,480
Thank you.

236
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:09,240
You're welcome.

237
00:11:43,360 --> 00:11:43,919
We found it.

238
00:11:44,159 --> 00:11:44,600
Yes.

239
00:11:44,879 --> 00:11:46,039
From our investigation, that motorcycle

240
00:11:46,039 --> 00:11:46,960
had fake plates.

241
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:48,440
The rider was also wearing a helmet,

242
00:11:48,720 --> 00:11:50,200
so we can't ID them yet.

243
00:11:50,519 --> 00:11:52,919
But we found a strange lead.

244
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:53,879
That bike

245
00:11:53,879 --> 00:11:55,399
once showed up at Jiang Lai's doorstep.

246
00:11:56,279 --> 00:11:57,000
Jiang Lai?

247
00:12:04,759 --> 00:12:06,399
Why'd you think to ask me to shop with you?

248
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:10,200
I just wanted to pick up a few clothes.

249
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,600
Aren't you doing that...

250
00:12:12,960 --> 00:12:14,159
fashion blogger thing?

251
00:12:14,519 --> 00:12:16,000
So I figured I'd ask a pro like you

252
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:16,639
for some advice.

253
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:17,679
Sure.

254
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:19,480
I can give advice,

255
00:12:20,279 --> 00:12:22,720
but why'd you bring me to a mall?

256
00:12:26,320 --> 00:12:27,759
Then... should we shop online?

257
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,120
You're really funny.

258
00:12:53,279 --> 00:12:54,399
Except for this plaid one,

259
00:12:54,600 --> 00:12:56,039
try on all the other clothes.

260
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:57,600
Okay, please wait a moment.

261
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:00,159
Where are you going?

262
00:13:00,919 --> 00:13:01,960
Aren't you going to try them on?

263
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:03,399
You planning to try them yourself?

264
00:13:03,639 --> 00:13:04,279
So many?

265
00:13:04,519 --> 00:13:05,200
Won't you get tired?

266
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:12,759
No.

267
00:13:13,440 --> 00:13:14,840
Can't you find a few more models?

268
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:16,279
So I can take my time looking.

269
00:13:16,279 --> 00:13:17,159
How long is this going to take?

270
00:13:17,519 --> 00:13:19,000
Understood, we'll be more careful next time.

271
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:20,879
But for fitting models,

272
00:13:20,879 --> 00:13:22,840
they need to match the VIP's height and weight,

273
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:24,120
with the same leg and arm length.

274
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:25,159
They're really hard to find.

275
00:13:25,519 --> 00:13:26,879
So this one you found matches, then?

276
00:13:27,279 --> 00:13:28,919
I pay you to meet my needs,

277
00:13:29,399 --> 00:13:31,000
not to listen to you waste my time here

278
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:31,759
making excuses.

279
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:32,720
Yes, yes, yes.

280
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:34,080
We'll switch someone out right away.

281
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:37,399
You're pretty good at making things hard for people.

282
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:38,799
Making things hard?

283
00:13:39,480 --> 00:13:41,360
I'm giving them a chance to make money, okay?

284
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:43,080
Being able to enter this VIP room,

285
00:13:43,240 --> 00:13:44,519
they must be thrilled.

286
00:13:44,919 --> 00:13:45,679
As long as they get in,

